The paper proposes a novel neural network architecture for memory and relational reasoning, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of self-attention and associative memory suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI), while the application of the model to diverse tasks such as geometry, graph, reinforcement learning, and question answering suggests a broad scope that could also encompass computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the use of outer product and high-order relationships suggests a potential connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
